race.comment: CROSS TASMAN (7) has gone to a new level this prep and will relish the extra trip from the low draw. Great ride from the outside gate when demolishing his rivals over the 1300m in BM72 class at Randwick. Will appreciate some sting out of the ground and looks hard to stop. HEREWARD (16) talented three-year-old gelding who keeps raising the bar. Has a tricky gate to deal with today in this stronger contest but has the upside to make a real race of it. PIPPIE BEACH (1) proven third-up performer desperate for a rain affected track. Savaged the line when fourth in the G3 Belle Turf over 1600m at Gosford. Claim helps and she looks great each way value in this weaker contest. PURE ALPHA (9) frustrating gelding who excels second-up. Key jockey change from the low draw and can make rapid improvement.
